added.title: Jail Break
added.description: Steven teams up with a new ally to rescue the Gems.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: Mr. Greg
added.description: Steven, Greg and Pearl take a trip to Empire City to live the good life.

added.title: Hit the Diamond
added.description: Steven and the Gems play an old fashioned game of baseball.

added.title: Mindful Education
added.description: Steven and Connie need to learn greater focus to take their training to the next level.

added.title: Now We're Only Falling Apart
added.description: Pearl tells a story.

added.title: What's Your Problem?
added.description: Amethyst convinces Steven to take a day off for himself.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Steven shows some city slicker gems how the cowboys lived.

added.title: Castles and Kitties
added.description: Score Creeper traps the gang in a fantasy role playing game where they must follow a complex set of rules to win their freedom.

added.title: Brain Trust
added.description: Dr. Fox accidentally transports the gang inside her brain, where they must control her movements to complete a dangerous experiment.

added.title: Friend Wars
added.description: Princess SugarSalt dupes Axel into hanging out with Cleo LeBall and usurps his role as team leader, forcing Zoe to step in and keep the toys together.

added.title: That Slobot Is No Bot of Mine
added.description: Axel and the team compete against themselves in tests of skill, strength, and stamina, but when SloBot gets belittled, he splits into three separate robots - each with their own evil personalities!

added.title: Bowling for Ballers
added.description: Axel and the team must intervene when Zoe's not-so-friendly bowling competition with Cleo LeBall gets interrupted by Madcap, Porcupunk, and their new cohort, the mischievously magnetic Dynamo.

added.title: Countdown
added.description: Axel has to clean up the living room in time for his uncle's dinner party, but trying to do too much at once leaves him stuck as a toy with Orangutank on the loose and less than an hour until the guests arrive.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 1
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 2
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #BreakingNews
added.description: Lois Lane's attempt to get an internship at the Daily Planet leads to her trying to unmask the Super Hero Girls, which forces the girls to a battle of wits with their greatest nemesis yet.

added.title: #CrashCourse
added.description: When a high-speed chase breaks out during her driver's test, Diana Prince's desire to fight evil clashes with her desire to undergo a World of Man teenage rite of passage, getting her license.

added.title: Ahora nos estamos separando
added.description: Perla cuenta una historia.

added.title: Cual es tu problema
added.description: Amatista convence a Steven de que se tome un día libre.

added.title: La pregunta
added.description: Steven les muestra a unas gemas citadinas cómo vivían los vaqueros.

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Primera parte
added.description: En el episodio estreno de cuatro partes de la serie, seis chicas comunes y corrientes se conocen y descubren que tienen poderes extraordinarios. Deciden unir sus fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Segunda parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 2 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Haunted House/Two of a Kind
added.description: Haunted House: Rumor has it that there's a haunted building in Los Volmos, and the Awesome Brawlers are on the case! Who doesn't like a good ghost hunt, plus capturing a ghost on camera should make Awesome Brawlers' next video a huge success!/Two of a Kind: Veronica Venegas is doing a special report on the Awesome brawlers own: Lightening! The special report takes a back seat when Lightening is challenged to a brawl. Lightening uses this brawl the perfect opportunity to rollout his new Bakugan partner: Tretorous.

removed.title: Alone Together
removed.description: The Gems try to teach Steven to use his fusion powers.

removed.title: Too Cool
removed.description: Puppycorn needs a lesson in how to be cool. The gang is more than happy to teach him, until his coolness unexpectedly freezes the whole kingdom.

removed.title: Old Lady Bodyguard
removed.description: After being "bought" at a charity auction, Hawkodile is forced to spend the day as Old Lady Edith's personal bodyguard.

removed.title: Awesome Brawlers Training  Camp
removed.description: The Awesome Brawlers head to a training facility owned by Kasami International to prepare for the Bakugan Battle League - Los Volmos. But once the gang figures out they will all be competing against each other for the same title, the "team building" retreat doesn't quite go as planned./Agit turns up at the Kasami training facility and fits right in with the Awesome brawlers. This is a lifestyle that he can get used to, but it becomes apparent Agit is torn between a life as a phantom thief and life as a brawler.
